---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Our Process — AB Brothers Construction"
  description="From the initial consultation to the final walkthrough. See how AB Brothers Construction handles every project with transparency, daily schedules, and clear budgets."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <img src="/images/additions-images-1.png" alt="" class="hero-bg" aria-hidden="true" fetchpriority="high" />
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content wrap">
      <span class="label">How We Work</span>
      <h1>Our Process</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub text-dim">
        Straightforward, transparent, and on schedule from day one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process Steps -->
  <section class="steps-section">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
      <p class="steps-intro text-dim reveal">
        We're proud to be one of Pittsburgh's premier home builders. Our process keeps things clear so you always know what's happening, what's next, and what it costs.
      </p>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">01</span>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Initial Consultation</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              Andy and Bob meet you at your home, walk the space, and listen to what you want. We discuss goals, budget, and timeline to make sure we're the right fit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">02</span>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Detailed Quote & Schedule</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              You receive a detailed quote and a day-by-day schedule of all work. No surprises. We also help pick fixtures, tile, and materials so you can make confident decisions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">03</span>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Prep & Protection</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              We use floor and wall coverings, plastic zipper walls, and protective barriers to keep your home clean and safe during the project. Your home gets the same respect we'd give our own.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">04</span>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Skilled Daily Work</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              Every task is performed by certified tradesmen, by code. Your home is cleaned at the end of every workday. Bob oversees each day's progress.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">05</span>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Quality Materials</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              Top-of-the-line building supplies for every aspect of your renovation. It costs a little more upfront, but it lasts longer and increases your home's value.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <span class="step-num">06</span>
          </div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Final Walkthrough</h3>
            <p class="text-dim">
              We walk through the completed project together. Every detail is reviewed. We don't consider the job finished until you do.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Testimonial break -->
  <section class="quote-section section--surface">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow reveal">
      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        <div class="pullquote-bar"></div>
        <p>
          "I'm so glad AB Brothers was recommended to me. Their communication was great, they worked long hours to make sure my family wasn't without our main bathroom for too long, and the finished job exceeded my expectations. It's been over 3 years and everything still looks great."
        </p>
        <footer>
          <cite>Jill McKibben Suley</cite>
        </footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
      <div class="faq-header reveal">
        <span class="label">Common Questions</span>
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>How long will I be without plumbing or electrical?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-answer text-dim">
            You will only be without plumbing or electrical on certain days, for a few hours up to one whole day.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>How long does a typical project take?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-answer text-dim">
            Every job is different. Typically a bathroom is 3-4 weeks, a kitchen 4-6 weeks, and an average size addition 3-4 months.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Can you provide a quote over the phone?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-answer text-dim">
            We can't price a job before an in-home consultation because each job is different. We need to see the space and understand your specific needs before providing an accurate estimate.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Do you do all the work yourself?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-answer text-dim">
            Most of the project is done in-house with AB Brothers Construction. For electrical, drywall finishing, and HVAC, we have a small group of trusted and licensed tradesmen we've used since the start of our business.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Who will be my main point of contact?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-answer text-dim">
            Andrew and Bob work closely with each customer during planning. Bob is the project manager and your main contact for the duration of the job.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section section--surface">
    <div class="wrap" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 class="reveal">Ready to Get Started?</h2>
      <p class="text-dim reveal" style="max-width: 30rem; margin: 1.25rem auto 2rem;">
        Contact us to schedule a consultation. We'll walk through your vision and give you a clear plan.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--copper reveal">Schedule a Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 45vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    padding-block: 6rem 3rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to right,
      var(--dark) 35%,
      color-mix(in oklch, var(--dark) 65%, transparent)
    );
  }

  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .hero h1 { margin-top: 0.75rem; }

  .hero-sub {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 28rem;
  }

  /* Steps */
  .steps-section {
    padding-block: var(--section-y);
  }

  .steps-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .step:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .step-marker {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--copper);
    line-height: 1;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 3rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border: 2px solid var(--copper);
  }

  .step-line {
    width: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .step-body h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .step-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Testimonial */
  .quote-section {
    padding-block: var(--section-y);
  }

  .pullquote {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .pullquote-bar {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 3px;
    background: var(--copper);
  }

  .pullquote p {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .pullquote cite {
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--copper);
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section {
    padding-block: var(--section-y);
  }

  .faq-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .faq-header h2 {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .faq-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .faq-question {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    font-weight: 700;
    list-style: none;

    &::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  }

  .faq-icon {
    width: 1.25rem;
    height: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 1rem;

    &::before,
    &::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      background: var(--copper);
      transition: transform 0.3s;
    }

    &::before {
      width: 100%;
      height: 2px;
      top: 50%;
      left: 0;
      transform: translateY(-50%);
    }

    &::after {
      width: 2px;
      height: 100%;
      left: 50%;
      top: 0;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
    }
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-icon::after {
    transform: translateX(-50%) rotate(90deg);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-section {
    padding-block: var(--section-y);
  }
</style>
